-- Berlusconi Says New Italian Industry Ministry Will Be Appointed Next Week
-- Flavia Krause-Jackson
-- 2010-07-23T13:02:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/berlusconi-says-new-italian-industry-ministry-will-be-appointed-next-week.html

          
          
             Italian Prime Minister Silvio
Berlusconi said today that his government will appoint a new
industry minister next week.  
 Berlusconi took over as interim industry minister after
Claudio Scajola, a close ally, resigned on May 4 amid a scandal
over his purchase of a home in Rome.  
 Berlusconi spoke at a news conference in Milan.  
          
          


  


        